.TH "TEMPORAL.NOW" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.Now \- Temporal.Now
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Temporal.Now\f[B]\f[R] namespace object contains static
methods for getting the current time in various formats.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Unlike most global objects, \f[CR]Temporal.Now\f[R] is not a
constructor.
You cannot use it with the \f[CR]new\f[R] operator or invoke the
\f[CR]Temporal.Now\f[R] object as a function.
All properties and methods of \f[CR]Temporal.Now\f[R] are static (just
like the \f[CR]Math\f[R] object).
.PP
Most fundamentally, the system time is returned by the operating system
as a time since the Unix epoch (usually millisecond\-level precision,
but might be nanosecond\-level too).
\f[CR]Temporal.Now.instant()\f[R] returns this time as a
\f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object.
.PP
An instant can be interpreted in a time zone (which is the system time
zone \f[CR]Temporal.Now.timeZoneId()\f[R] by default) in the same
fashion as \f[CR]Temporal.Instant.prototype.toZonedDateTimeISO()\f[R].
To get a \f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] object, you can use
\f[CR]Temporal.Now.zonedDateTimeISO()\f[R].
You can also get different parts of the date and time, using
\f[CR]Temporal.Now.plainDateISO()\f[R],
\f[CR]Temporal.Now.plainTimeISO()\f[R], and
\f[CR]Temporal.Now.plainDateTimeISO()\f[R].
.PP
For example, if the computer is set to the time zone
\(lqAmerica/New_York\(rq, \f[CR]Temporal.Now.zonedDateTimeISO()\f[R]
returns a zoned date\-time like:
\f[CR]2021\-08\-01T10:40:12.345\-04:00[America/New_York]\f[R].
In this case, \f[CR]Temporal.Now.plainTimeISO()\f[R] would return the
time part of this zoned date\-time: \f[CR]10:40:12.345\f[R].
However, if you call \f[CR]Temporal.Now.plainTimeISO(\(dqUTC\(dq)\f[R],
it returns the time part of the zoned date\-time in the UTC time zone:
\f[CR]14:40:12.345\f[R].
This is especially useful for cross\-system communication where the
other end may be expecting the time in a different time zone.
.SS Reduced time precision
To offer protection against timing attacks and fingerprinting, the
precision of the \f[CR]Temporal.Now\f[R] functions might get rounded
depending on browser settings.
In Firefox, the \f[CR]privacy.reduceTimerPrecision\f[R] preference is
enabled by default and defaults to 2ms.
You can also enable \f[CR]privacy.resistFingerprinting\f[R], in which
case the precision will be 100ms or the value of
\f[CR]privacy.resistFingerprinting.reduceTimerPrecision.microseconds\f[R],
whichever is larger.
.PP
For example, with reduced time precision, the result of
\f[CR]Temporal.Now.instant().epochMilliseconds\f[R] will always be a
multiple of 2, or a multiple of 100 (or
\f[CR]privacy.resistFingerprinting.reduceTimerPrecision.microseconds\f[R])
with \f[CR]privacy.resistFingerprinting\f[R] enabled.
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// reduced time precision (2ms) in Firefox 60\f[R]
Temporal.Now.instant().epochMilliseconds;
\f[I]// Might be:\f[R]
\f[I]// 1519211809934\f[R]
\f[I]// 1519211810362\f[R]
\f[I]// 1519211811670\f[R]
\f[I]// \&...\f[R]

\f[I]// reduced time precision with \(gaprivacy.resistFingerprinting\(ga enabled\f[R]
Temporal.Now.instant().epochMilliseconds;
\f[I]// Might be:\f[R]
\f[I]// 1519129853500\f[R]
\f[I]// 1519129858900\f[R]
\f[I]// 1519129864400\f[R]
\f[I]// \&...\f[R]
.EE
.SH STATIC PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.Now[Symbol.toStringTag]\f[R]
The initial value of the \f[CR][Symbol.toStringTag]\f[R] property is the
string \f[CR]\(dqTemporal.Now\(dq\f[R].
This property is used in \f[CR]Object.prototype.toString()\f[R].
.SH STATIC METHODS
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.Now.instant()\f[R]
Returns the current time as a \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.Now.plainDateISO()\f[R]
Returns the current date as a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object, in
the ISO 8601 calendar and the specified time zone.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.Now.plainDateTimeISO()\f[R]
Returns the current date and time as a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R]
object, in the ISO 8601 calendar and the specified time zone.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.Now.plainTimeISO()\f[R]
Returns the current time as a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R] object, in
the specified time zone.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.Now.timeZoneId()\f[R]
Returns a time zone identifier representing the system\(cqs current time
zone.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.Now.zonedDateTimeISO()\f[R]
Returns the current date and time as a \f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R]
object, in the ISO 8601 calendar and the specified time zone.
